Suicides are one of the leading causes of death from injuries in the Republic of Croatia. As a major public health issue, suicide remains a growing national concern with the suicide rates in Croatia being among the highest in the world. In 2016, Croatia was the 16th highest ranking country globally and 8th in the EU when it came to suicide with an average overall (both male and female) suicide rate of 16 per 1,00,000 population (1, 2). Moreover, when compared to other causes of death in Croatia, death by suicide is ranked among the top 10 most frequent causes of death.
